 e^x = 1 
x\!=\! N 2\pi i
N\!=\!1,2,3\dots
e^{ix}=\cos(x)+i\sin(x).
\cos(x)+i\sin(x)
[\cos(x), \sin(x)]
e^{ix+y}=e^y(\cos(x)+i\sin(x)).
y
[e^y\cos(x), e^y\sin(x)]
\forall n\in \mathbb Z
e^{i2\pi n}= \cos(2\pi n)+i\sin(2\pi n)=1+i0=1
